body:
Can remove the `active_spkms` lookup by using `desc_spkm->IsRange()`.
E.g.
```c++
for (auto spkm : m_wallet.GetAllScriptPubKeyMans()) {
     auto desc_spkm{dynamic_cast<DescriptorScriptPubKeyMan*>(spkm)};
     AddScriptPubKeys(desc_spkm);
     // save each spkm range end for possible future filter updates
     if (desc_spkm->IsRange()) {
         m_last_range_ends.emplace(desc_spkm->GetID(), GetDescriptorRangeEnd(*desc_spkm));
     }
}
```

Note: `IsRange()` can be a simple:
```c++
bool DescriptorScriptPubKeyMan::IsRange()
{
   return WITH_LOCK(cs_desc_man, return GetWalletDescriptor().descriptor->IsRange());
}
```

